cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DC 

This paper is primarily focused on achieving differential privacy in data analysis, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of DP programs on encrypted data, which is related to database systems (cs.DB). The authors propose a programming framework for DP, which involves logical DP programs, and this is related to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses performance optimizations, which is related to computer systems and networking (cs.CY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
